Russia told the United Nations Security Council on Thursday that there was still no agreement on a 30-day UN ceasefire in Syria. Most Security Council members have been urging a vote on the proposal, which has languished since February 9, amid fierce fighting in the opposition-held enclave of eastern Ghouta. Read more: UN pleads for ceasefire in Syria's Ghouta as over 300 dead in strikes What happened? Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
